 fee.\n|{{yes|\u221a}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Cyprus}}\n| {{yes|Visa not required}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=US|destination=CY|accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/consular02_en/consular02_en?OpenDocument|title=Travel Information for Foreign Visitors to Cyprus|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140323194207/http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2006.nsf/consular02_en/consular02_en?OpenDocument|archivedate=2014-03-23}}</ref>\n| {{ntsh|90}}90 days\n|\n*Admission temporarily refused until March 30, 2020 due to the outbreak of 2019-nCoV in the United States.<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Travel_restrictions_related_to_the_2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_pandemic#Countries_implementing_a_global_travel_ban</ref>\n*90 days within any 180-day period<ref>{{cite web|title=Cyprus Country Specific Information \u2013 Entry/Exit Requirements for U.S. Citizens|url=https://travel.state.gov/content/passports/en/country/cyprus.html|publisher=Bureau of Consular Affairs, U.S. Department of State|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref> Beginning in January 2021, [[ETIAS]] system will become mandatory for all Non-EU international travellers.<ref name=\"europa.eu-1\"/><ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\"/>\n|{{no|X}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Czech Republic}}\n| {{yes|Visa not required}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=US|destination=CZ|accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/jnp/en/information_for_aliens/general_visa_information/index.html|title=General visa information for Czech Republic|publisher=}}</ref>\n| {{ntsh|90}}90 days\n|\n* 90 days within any 180-day period in the [[Schengen Area]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Czech Republic Country Specific Information \u2013 Entry/Exit Requirements for U.S. Citizens|url=https://travel.state.gov/content/passports/en/country/czech-republic.html|publisher=Bureau of Consular Affairs, U.S. Department of State|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref> Beginning in January 2021, [[ETIAS]] system will beco